    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## linkedin-hq creator feed v2 — with auto-comment\n\n**Sequential flow:**\n1. Schedule trigger every 4h\n2. Read linkedin_creators from the linkedin-hq Config tab\n3. Apify scrape latest posts from each creator\n4. Aggregate + normalize into intel item shape\n5. POST to /api/intel/ingest — writes scraped posts to the Intel tab (for /news display)\n6. POST to /api/comments/plan — Vercel reads the Intel tab, picks LinkedIn posts that don't yet have a comment, generates one comment per post via Claude, runs the voice quality gate, writes the draft comment_text + comment_status='draft' + comment_style straight into the matching Intel row's new comment columns, returns the approved comments to n8n\n7. Split returned comments into individual items\n8. Random 30-90s wait per item (humanize cadence — never burst-post all 5 in 2 seconds)\n9. POST each comment to LinkedIn /v2/socialActions/{urn}/comments via the existing OAuth credential\n10. Branch on success (201) vs failure\n11. Log result back to /api/comments/log → updates the matching Intel row's comment_status to 'posted' or 'post_failed' (looked up by URL)\n12. Slack notify the #linkedin-comments channel either way\n\n**Why this design:**\n- One row per LinkedIn post in Intel, with comment data attached. No separate Comments tab. You can scan the Intel tab and see exactly which posts have a comment and which don't, in one place.\n- Daily cap (default 5) is enforced by /api/comments/plan reading the Intel tab. Once 5 posts today have comment_status='posted', /plan returns an empty list and posts nothing until tomorrow.\n- Dedup is automatic — /plan only picks rows where comment_status is empty.\n\n**Hardcoded values:**\n- LINKEDIN_HQ ingest token: `REPLACE_WITH_INGEST_TOKEN`\n- LinkedIn person URN: `urn:li:person:CYH_eYFiZb` (Taha)\n- Apify token: existing leaked one\n- LinkedIn OAuth credential: `LinkedIn account` (id `Dg0fNXlvpYL0WwHR`, same as parasite flow)\n- Slack credential: `sophiya-slack-connection` (id `4mJJu3Vcba9QnUDR`, same as parasite flow)\n- Slack channel: `linkedin-comments` — create this in your workspace before activating\n\n**To kill a bad comment**: open the post URL from the Slack notification → delete the comment from LinkedIn UI → manually update the matching Intel row's comment_status to `deleted`.",
        "height": 600,
        "width": 800
      },
